You need to migrate your production PostgreSQL RDS instance to a larger instance type without downtime. What approach would you take?
To migrate a production PostgreSQL RDS instance to a larger instance type without downtime, I would take the following approach:
1. Create a read replica of the existing PostgreSQL RDS instance.
2. Once the read replica is fully synchronized, promote it to be the new primary instance.
3. Update the application configuration to point to the new primary instance.
4. Finally, modify the original RDS instance to the desired larger instance type and set it up as a read replica of the new primary.
This approach ensures continuous availability during the migration process.
5. Use RDS Multi-AZ deployments to ensure high availability during the migration.

